node.text: Join me in my #2Days200Dollars challenge by choosing any space in your home to makeover in 2 days with just 200 dollars!  This is a fun challenge meant to inspire you to take action and create a space you love without taking tons of time or money.  Let's get started 👊😘 Be sure to share what you're doing by tagging me @cynthia_harper_ and I'll choose some of my favorite transformations to share in my stories/posts/blog! 🙌

node.text: Ask yourself these questions to help free yourself from unnecessary clutter and get ready to simplify your home!

node.title: Shifting Our Mindset Toward a Simpler Home

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Cynthia Harper on August 27, 2021 tagging @amazonhome. May be an image of living room.

node.text: Remember that time my coffee table leg kept breaking and I just kept using hot glue to fix it?!  Because I'm fancy like that 😂  Well I decided it was finally time for an upgrade so I ordered this table from @amazonhome!  Now I can actually put things on my coffee table again without it tipping over.  It's the little things, ya know? 😉💛 #founditonamazon #amazonhome #ad

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Cynthia Harper on August 26, 2021 tagging @etsy, @target, @avalonflooring, and @cafeappliances. May be an image of 1 person and kitchen.

node.text: Simple & affordable changes are my favorite!   I was tired of the dark rustic wood (swipe to see the Before pic), so for just $11 and about an hour of my time, I was able to give this a lighter, more modern look.  And I love it!  Sometimes the answer to loving a home more isn't necessarily ripping things out or buying new things.  Sometimes it's as simple as breathing new life into what's already there.  Now excuse me while I go wood bleach all the things 😉

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Cynthia Harper on August 26, 2021 tagging @etsy, @target, @avalonflooring, and @cafeappliances. May be an image of 1 person and kitchen.
Photo by Cynthia Harper on August 26, 2021. May be an image of kitchen.
Photo shared by Cynthia Harper on August 20, 2021 tagging @target, and @grovecollaborative. May be an image of 1 person, standing and kitchen.

node.text: It worked!  Sometimes it just takes a little something to make a space feel fresh & new.  Like these lighter shelves 😍 Which now have me cleaning & restyling this whole space!  I picked up some Grove Co. items at @target because I've been switching to clean & sustainable brands, and now that Grove Co.’s best-sellers are available at Target, it makes it easy to stay stocked up.  I love simple changes and this project has me excited to get back into a more regular routine as the kids head back to school soon! Check out your local Target or target.com to get your favorite Grove Co. products.  #grovepartner #TargetXGroveCo @grovecollaborative

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Cynthia Harper on August 12, 2021 tagging @amazon. May be an image of 2 people, child and indoor.

node.text: I’m not going to lie…after a year of virtual school, we are all pretty excited to get back to regular school this year! #ad You might have thought it was Christmas morning when our box of school supplies from @amazon arrived, lol.  Amazon's Back to School storefront is so convenient to be able to order everything we need in one place and Prime members can take advantage of fast & free delivery for everything you need this school year.  Head to stories to see some of the kids' picks from the Back to School storefront.  As a mom, it’s so reassuring to see their enthusiasm for the upcoming school year.  And honestly as much as I loved the “bonus” time with them at home last year, I’m also ready to settle into a routine and watch them as they soar back out in the world.  It’s long overdue!  Head to amazon.com/backtoschool to stock up on everything you need this school year! #BackToSchooWithASmile #PrimeLife

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Cynthia Harper on August 11, 2021 tagging @dropps, @homedepot, @muddyheart, @amazon, and @gypsylaineliving. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: It's almost done.  I had 2 goals for this laundry room reno:  1) That it wouldn't look like anyone else's laundry room. I wanted it to be original & unique.  2) That I could create a modern-meets-old-world earthy organic vibe, while working within the existing footprint.  Despite having to pivot several times (remember the brick debacle 😳), I still think I accomplished it.  Adding these @gypsylaineliving handles to our handmade cabinet was the icing on the cake today.  I cannot get over how far this room has come...even if it's taken 6 months 😂 Swipe to see a reminder of what this view looked like when I started in February.  It's important to remember where we started, so we can appreciate how far we've come.  In DIY...in life...all of it. 💛   Xo, Cynthia

node.text: The posts & string lights are DONE!!! 🎇  Happy birthday to me 🎉  This all started because Chris decided to surprise me with a belated birthday gift.  He remembered how much I had raved about a similar set up when we were eating outside at a restaurant a few months ago.  And he decided to put those posts in the ground so that I could bring it to life right here in our own back yard.   This project was work.  Just like marriage is work.  But it's here.  It's done.  It's standing.  And we're still standing.  This may not be the most elaborate back patio but I love it, and it's 1,000 times better than before, and a place to make future memories.  And for that I am grateful 💛  xo, Cynthia

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Cynthia Harper on July 20, 2021 tagging @dropps, @homedepot, @behrpaint, @oldnavy, and @amazon. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text: I went bold with this warm "Rio Rust" paint for the win 🙌  The third time is a charm, right?!   It may have taken countless samples and multiple attempts, but this rich warm hue on the cabinet adds so much depth to the room.  And I love that it's DIFFERENT!   For me this cabinet color felt like a risk on such a large piece of furniture. It required me to step out of my normal comfort zone.  But I love how it turned out!   And at the end of the day, it's just paint. So I'm glad I went for it!  The cabinet clearly isn't done yet: I need to finish the bottom section, adjust the top hinges so the doors aren't crooked, and add shelves inside.  But I knew you guys wanted to see the paint color so I couldn't keep you waiting any longer 😘  Thanks for cheering me on these past few weeks as we've been buiding this 8 ft 4 inch cabinet.  It's not been easy but I'm hoping in the end I can say it was worth it 💛  Xo, Cynthia

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cynthia Harper on June 23, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, footwear and indoor.

node.text: The stairs are DONE 🎉  But here's a moment of raw honesty:  What you see is a smiling face and beautiful new stairwell.  And normal Instagram protocol would make this a celebratory post of a project completed.  Don't get me wrong, I am truly proud of how this budget friendly makeover turned out.  But I almost feel fake putting this smiling image up when I'm struggling through some hard things in real life.  So this post is dedicated to putting one foot in front of the other.  To showing up and creating beauty & joy when it's lacking.  To continuing to work hard to make things better...in my home...and in my life.  Thanks for all the love, support, and kindness you've shown throughout this project.  You guys have been more of a lifeline than you know ❤  xo, Cynthia

node.text: Part 1 of the stairs is DONE 👏🎉   I could swipe back and forth between this Before & After all day long.  It's crazy what a difference some paint and a good runner can make!  This project wasn't originally on my list but I needed a simple project to be my therapy right now.  And working creatively with my hands definitely lifts my spirits a bit.  This view from the top of the stairs might make things look finished, but there's still a bottom section of stairs to complete and the railings to DIY.  I'm grateful to keep working on this.  It's gonna be good!

node.text: Her in those sunglasses is such a vibe 🍍✌ And it pretty much sums up my level of excitement about @amazon Prime Day coming up on June 21 & 22! #Ad  I admire that Amazon has made it easy to support small businesses on #PrimeDay while still enjoying that fast, free delivery we all know and love.  One of my fave small businesses is @beeswrap which is owned by a mom of 3 that creates reusable food wraps from beeswax to help reduce single-use plastic waste and live more sustainably.  Have you heard of beeswax food wraps?  I was initially a little skeptical of how they'd work but they're durable, can be washed with soap and water, and reused for up to a year (head to my stories for a tutorial).  This year, Prime members who spend $10 on select small business products from June 7-20, get a $10 credit to spend on #PrimeDay. Head to amazon.com/supportsmall to learn more! #PrimeLife

node.text: A peep of my stair runner progress, aka: today's therapy session 🙌  I decided to stray from my all-neutral tendencies, and try a little color instead.  And I love it!!!   These colors, this fun pattern...it makes me feel happy.  I've got a lot of stairs left to finish, but I'm grateful for this project as a much-needed creative outlet right now.  I know I already said this in stories, but thank you for all your supportive & kind DMs last night. You guys are the best community of people, and you mean more to me than you know ❤  xo, Cynthia

node.text: From a blank porch wall...to a hanging herb garden 🌱  I really wanted a large garden this year, but I honestly just don't have the energy.  So instead I decided to create a hanging herb garden on this existing porch wall.  #ad I figured if it's front & center on my porch, I can't forget to water it regularly (which is usually my problem, lol😂).  I created cute little labels from paint stir sticks and my @officialcricut machine, and added them to these planters.  Then I screwed them onto my existing porch wall, and now I've got my very own cute & practical herb garden that I can tend to & nurture all summer long! 👊  #cricutmade
